{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/iochannelref\/init(unix:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Initializer","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"unix","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"title":"init(unix:)","externalID":"s:4GLib12IOChannelRefV4unixACSi_tcfc","extendedModule":"GLib","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"init","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a new ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","type":"reference"},{"text":" given a file descriptor. On UNIX systems","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this works for plain files, pipes, and sockets."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"unix"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"fd"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The returned ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" has a reference count of 1."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default encoding for "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel"},{"text":" is UTF-8. If your application","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is reading output from a command using via pipe, you may need to set"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the encoding to the encoding of the current locale (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_get_charset()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"By default, the fd passed will not be closed when the final reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannel","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" data structure is dropped.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to read raw binary data without interpretation, then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_io_channel_set_encoding()"},{"text":" function with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"encoding argument."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This function is available in GLib on Windows, too, but you should","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"avoid using it on Windows. The domain of file descriptors and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"sockets overlap. There is no way for GLib to know which one you mean"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in case the argument you pass to this function happens to be both a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"valid file descriptor and socket. If that happens a warning is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"issued, and GLib assumes that it is the file descriptor you mean."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOChannelRef"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/IOC